  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Tuberculosis
Type:        Bacterial
Pathogen:    M. tuberculosis
Transmission:Airborne droplets
Symptoms:    Persistent cough, night sweats
Treatment:   6-9 month antibiotics
Deaths/yr:   1.6M
Vaccine:     Yes (BCG, partial)
Discovered:  1882

Disease:     Dengue
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Dengue virus
Transmission:Aedes mosquito
Symptoms:    Fever, severe joint pain, rash
Treatment:   Supportive care, fluids
Deaths/yr:   0.04M
Vaccine:     Yes (for previously infected)
Discovered:  1779

Disease:     Cholera
Type:        Bacterial
Pathogen:    Vibrio cholerae
Transmission:Contaminated water
Symptoms:    Profuse watery diarrhea, vomiting
Treatment:   Oral rehydration, antibiotics
Deaths/yr:   0.095M
Vaccine:     Yes
Discovered:  1854

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the periodic table?
A1: The periodic table organizes 118 elements by atomic
     number. Elements in the same column share chemical
     properties. Rows are periods; columns are groups.

Q2: What is the speed of light?
A2: The speed of light in a vacuum is 299,792,458 meters
     per second (approximately 300,000 km/s), denoted as c.

Q3: What is plate tectonics?
A3: Earth's crust is divided into tectonic plates that move
     on the mantle. Their interactions create earthquakes,
     volcanoes, mountains, and ocean trenches over millions
     of years.

Q4: What is osmosis?
A4: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

Q5: What is democracy?
A5: Democracy is government where power derives from the
     people through free elections, rule of law, and
     protection of minority rights. Types include direct and
     representative democracy.

